# Credit Card Transaction Report - Tableau Analysis

## 📊 Project Overview

This project features a dynamic Tableau dashboard designed to monitor and analyze credit card transaction activities. It provides a deep dive into revenue streams, transaction volumes, and interest earnings, allowing stakeholders to track financial performance across different card tiers and transaction methods.

## 🗂️ Project Structure

* **Credit Card Transaction Report.twbx**: A Tableau Packaged Workbook containing the processed data extract and the visual dashboards.
* **Key Metrics**: Revenue, Transaction Count, Total Interest Earned, and Transaction Amount.

## 🚀 Key Insights & Dashboards

The workbook is structured to answer critical business questions:

* **Revenue Trends**: Analysis of weekly and monthly revenue growth.
* **Expenditure Analysis**: Breakdown of spending by category (e.g., Bills, Entertainment, Fuel, Grocery, Food, and Travel).
* **Card Tier Performance**: Comparative analysis of revenue generated by Blue, Silver, Gold, and Platinum cardholders.
* **Transaction Methods**: Insights into how customers pay (Swipe, Chip, or Online).
* **Demographic Revenue**: Revenue distribution based on education level, job type, and gender.

## 🛠️ Technical Details

* **Software**: Tableau Desktop / Tableau Public
* **File Format**: `.twbx` (Packaged Workbook)
* **Data Source**: Financial transaction records (integrated via extract).

## 📈 Sample Observations

* **High-Volume Categories**: Identification of which expenditure types (e.g., Bills or Groceries) contribute the most to the total transaction volume.
* **Method Preference**: Analysis showing whether "Swipe" transactions remain dominant over "Online" transactions.
* **Tier Contribution**: Evaluation of the "Blue" card tier vs. premium tiers in terms of interest and fee revenue.

## 📖 How to Open

1. **Clone or Download** this repository.
2. Install [Tableau Desktop](https://www.tableau.com/products/desktop) or the free [Tableau Reader](https://www.tableau.com/products/reader).
3. Open `Credit Card Transaction Report.twbx` to interact with the filters (Quarter, Gender, Card Type, etc.).
4. Alternatively, if published, you can view the live version on **Tableau Public** (https://public.tableau.com/app/profile/amrita.saha8026/viz/CreditCardTransactionReport_17582694452560/Dashboard1).
